The Lorentz Force Equation

The Lorentz Force is the combination of the electric and magnetic force exerted on a point charge due to electric and magnetic fields.

\textbf{F} = q \textbf{E} + q \textbf{v} \times \textbf{B}

where:

\textbf{F} [var. vec. LorentzForce, M L T^{-2}, N] is the Lorentz Force
q [var. scal. Charge, Q, C] is the charge of the particle
\textbf{E} [var. vec. ElectricField, M L T^{-2} Q^{-1}, N C^{-1}] is the electric field
\textbf{v} [var. vec. Velocity, L T^{-1}, m s^{-1}] is the velocity of the particle
\textbf{B} [var. vec. MagneticField, M T^{-1} Q^{-1}, T] is the magnetic field


